records.addlTxt:
Defendant Shawn L Overton in court with attorney Daniel E Meylink.  Defendant Shawn L Overton in custody.  Joy Hammond appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.

AS TO COUNT 2:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of the State, Court ordered count dismissed and read-in.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 11 days time served.  Huber privileges under Sec.303.08 Wis. Stats. to apply.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 1 YEAR.
Conditions: 
*  Full time student/obtain GED/HSED;
*  AODA assesment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  Establish paternity for any minor children;
*  Successfully complete a parenting class;
*  Possess no firearms;
*  Court will waive any costs and surcharges that can be waived.  Court ordered the defendant to pay any  costs and surcharges that can not be waived;
*  Serve 90 days in the House of Correction; STRAIGHT TIME;
*  Submit DNA sample.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
